The paper deals with a multiagent variant of the knapsack problem, which involves selecting a subset of items that satisfies the preferences of multiple voters. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the fields of game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
